PROBLEM: three visual worlds on one site. Live Cell OS had the industrial
cell; Robot Execution still showed the primitive black-cylinder gantry; the
other five demos floated on a bare grid. No shared status language.

SOLUTION: components/demos/IndustrialCell.tsx — the single source for the
plant vocabulary, consumed by every scene:
- PalletizerArm: the SAME 4-axis IK arm everywhere (parameterized by pallet,
  origin, deck height; hold + wear props). Robot Execution's primitive gantry
  (112 lines) deleted and replaced — the arm the user fights in Live Cell OS
  is the arm that executes their edited plan.
- Conveyor: shared infeed, auto-aligned to the arm's pick station.
- AndonTower: the UNIVERSAL status lamp on all 7 demos — green stable plan /
  cell idle, blue executing, amber warnings or exception handling, red
  unstable plan or FAULT_ESTOP. Production/E-comm/Multi/Twin wire it to live
  validation, Robot goes blue while running, Stress goes red on topple and
  amber on >25mm settle shift, Live Cell OS maps the edge state machine.
- CellFloor + SafetyFence + fog on every canvas, including the Rapier physics
  scene — one lighting/background language site-wide.
- All environment meshes have raycast disabled: drag-and-drop demos keep
  working on top of the plant.
- CellScene deduplicated (~300 lines) onto the shared kit; multi-pallet lamps
  are per-pallet.

Verified: next build clean; shared-arm IK regression (0 NaN, 0 reach clamps
over pick + far-corner targets at both deck heights)
